frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Patient to be more strong, often resulting in something that is more secure and safe.
A Recipient comes into possession of the Theme as a result of the joint action of the Donor and the Recipient.
An Entity is presented as having been seen or experienced by a (typically generic and backgrounded)
A Topical_entity has properties which are affected by the existence and association of an Entity.
In this frame an Experiencer experiences an Emotion or is in an Emotional_state.
Individuals first encounter each other and make introductions at a particular Time, Place, or Context.
frameExamples: Local Serbs are <t>strengthening</t> their grip on a narrow corridor along the Sava River between two large Serbian areas.

Susanna Fulton's work is <t>new</t> to me.

listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> fortifies the <fen>Patient</fen>.

The deviation of the actual level of recognizability of the <fen>Entity</fen> from the level specified by the target.
Some entity, abstract or concrete, which is stated to exist and be associated with the <fen>Topical_entity</fen>.
The entity under discussion, whose states and properties are impacted by its association with the <fen>Entity</fen>.

The <fen>Emotional_state</fen> is the state the <fen>Experiencer</fen> is in.
The <fen>Evaluation</fen> is a negative or positive assessment of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> regarding his or her <fen>Emotional_state</fen>.
The persons (or in rare cases animals) that make each other's acquaintance.
The semantically more prominent one of the two parties when the Individuals are realized separately.
The semantically less prominent of the two parties when the <fen>Individuals</fen> are expressed separately.
The time when the Individuals make each other's acquaintance.
The location where the Individuals make each others acquaintance.
